                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.1121 Hirsch, Helmut/14: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-21T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 21, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Your number 77, April 20, 4 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d294fn4">Not
                        printed.</note> Investigation shows that Helmut Hirsch is an American
                    citizen. You are authorized to communicate this information to the German
                    officials, and do whatever is possible to prevent any injustice to the
                    party.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
